title: Gracia Larsen-Schmidt
text:
Hello! My name is Gracia Larsen-Schmidt. I am a senior at St. Olaf College majoring in English with concentrations in Statistics and Data Science, Race and Ethnic Studies, and Gender and Sexuality Studies. I run cross country and track collegiately and am the captain of my cross country team. I am a member and the president of Agnes A Cappella, the treble-voice a cappella group on campus. I work as a writing tutor and anthropology student researcher. I am currently involved in statistics and data science research on milkweeds and local adaptation through St. Olaf’s Center for Interdisciplinary Research.
Take a look around this website to learn more about the work I have done so far in Data Science 2!
